# TASKS

> Shared task list across all agents. `@pm-agent` owns the structure.
> Each agent updates only its own rows. `## Notes` is append-only.
> See `.claude/agents/_base.md` for the full rules.

## Row format

```
- [ ] T### @<handle> [risk:<tier>] [size:<XS|S|M|L>] [#<issue>] <one-line deliverable> — <status>
      branch: <initials>/<agent>/<type>/T###-<slug>
      depends-on: [T###, T###]
      files: path/a, path/b
      artifact: <repo-relative-path the next gate will read>
```

- `risk:` — `low` | `medium` | `high` | `critical`
- `size:` — `XS` | `S` | `M` | `L`
- `branch:` — every task has its own fresh branch off `main`. No two tasks share a branch.
- `artifact:` — the file the next gate verifies before starting. PM uses it in the dispatch directive.
- Deliverables are nouns/states, not verbs. ("Settings page renders user email" not "Build settings page".)
- One owner per task. No dual ownership.

## Next dispatch

PM writes this section after each completion. One line: `@<next-handle> T### — branch <name> — verify artifact <path> — previous PR #<n> merged`. Orchestrator reads it, creates the branch from a clean `main`, and invokes the named agent.

## In Progress

Tasks currently being worked on. Move from Backlog when you start.

## Backlog

Tasks ready to pick up, in priority order (top = highest).

## Done

Completed tasks. Marked `[x]` with artifact link + date.

## Blocked

Tasks that hit a blocker. Note the cause inline.

## Notes

Append-only audit trail. Format: `YYYY-MM-DD @handle: message`.
